MOTORISTS faced travel chaos today after a two-bus crash in Glasgow City Centre.&nbsp;A McGills bus and a Stagecoach double decker collided outside the Citizen M Hotel in Renfrew Street.It happened at around 9am on Wednesday.There were delays for travellers during the rush hour, as the buses lay stationery in the road following the crash.Meanwhile, there were traffic problems in East Ayrshire following a crash on the A736.Drivers were delayed in both directions between the B778 and the B785 junctions.Police were directing traffic.